1
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:33,540
Dad, want some caramel?

2
00:02:33,540 --> 00:02:35,290
Oh, thanks.

3
00:02:35,290 --> 00:02:36,500
Aren't you tired?

4
00:02:36,500 --> 00:02:37,300
Nah.

5
00:02:37,300 --> 00:02:38,460
We're almost there.

6
00:02:50,180 --> 00:02:50,890
Mei, hide!

7
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:58,900
It wasn't a policeman.

8
00:02:58,900 --> 00:03:00,610
Hi!

9
00:03:31,560 --> 00:03:34,190
Are any of your folks around?

10
00:03:36,480 --> 00:03:37,610
Thanks.

11
00:03:39,860 --> 00:03:43,610
We're the Kusakabes!
We'll be moving in down the road!

12
00:03:44,410 --> 00:03:46,870
It's a pleasure to meet you!

13
00:03:46,870 --> 00:03:48,530
Welcome!

14
00:03:53,870 --> 00:03:55,080
Thank you.

15
00:04:17,190 --> 00:04:17,980
Well, this is it.

16
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:21,230
Hey, wait up!

17
00:04:23,860 --> 00:04:25,660
Mei, there's a bridge!

18
00:04:25,660 --> 00:04:26,780
A bridge?

19
00:04:31,990 --> 00:04:34,580
There's fish too! See those flashes of light?

20
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:36,790
So, how do you like it here?

21
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,840
Dad, it's so cool!

22
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,460
It's a tunnel of trees!

23
00:04:47,010 --> 00:04:48,010
Is that our house?

24
00:04:52,270 --> 00:04:54,060
Hurry up!

25
00:05:07,780 --> 00:05:08,820
It's a wreck!

26
00:05:08,820 --> 00:05:10,450
A wreck!

27
00:05:10,450 --> 00:05:12,120
Looks like a haunted house!

28
00:05:12,120 --> 00:05:12,910
Haunted?

29
00:05:20,670 --> 00:05:21,920
It's all rotten.

30
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,350
It's gonna fall down!

31
00:05:35,350 --> 00:05:37,060
It's gonna fall down!

32
00:05:47,070 --> 00:05:48,280
Mei, look at that!

33
00:05:48,280 --> 00:05:48,700
Huh?

34
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,030
Look!

35
00:06:01,580 --> 00:06:03,250
It's big, isn't it?

36
00:06:08,970 --> 00:06:11,390
Dad, there's a huge tree!

37
00:06:12,180 --> 00:06:13,930
Oh, it's a camphor tree.

38
00:06:16,060 --> 00:06:16,970
A camphor tree!

39
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:18,270
A camphor tree!

40
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:28,150
Whoops!

41
00:06:31,110 --> 00:06:31,700
An acorn.

42
00:06:34,620 --> 00:06:35,280
Let me see!

43
00:06:36,830 --> 00:06:38,250
Hey, another one!

44
00:06:44,290 --> 00:06:45,750
I got one!

45
00:06:51,800 --> 00:06:54,390
Hey, come on. I can't open the storm shutters.

46
00:06:55,140 --> 00:06:56,260
Acorns!

47
00:06:56,260 --> 00:06:58,680
There are acorns falling around in the house.

48
00:06:58,680 --> 00:07:00,140
They dropped from up there!

49
00:07:04,770 --> 00:07:07,650
I wonder if there are squirrels in here?

50
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:12,530
Or maybe it's rats that like acorns.

51
00:07:12,910 --> 00:07:13,700
What?!

52
00:07:13,700 --> 00:07:15,160
I'd rather have squirrels!

53
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:17,660
Where do you want to put this?

54
00:07:18,410 --> 00:07:20,710
Oh, over here. I'll get these shutters
opened all the way for you.

55
00:07:20,710 --> 00:07:22,710
Satsuki, can you open up the kitchen
around the back?

56
00:07:22,710 --> 00:07:23,540
Okay!

57
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:24,670
It should be easy to spot.

58
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:25,420
Yep.

59
00:07:27,550 --> 00:07:28,550
Come on, this way!

60
00:07:30,260 --> 00:07:31,670
Wait up!

61
00:07:33,220 --> 00:07:34,760
Come on, hurry up!

62
00:08:12,970 --> 00:08:13,800
Let's go.

63
00:08:13,800 --> 00:08:14,510
Yeah.

64
00:08:26,520 --> 00:08:27,400
The bath.

65
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:28,020
Yeah.

66
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,740
There's nothing here.

67
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:35,610
Yeah…

68
00:08:37,280 --> 00:08:38,620
That's the bathroom.

69
00:08:38,620 --> 00:08:40,530
Dad, there's something in here.

70
00:08:40,530 --> 00:08:41,490
A squirrel?

71
00:08:41,490 --> 00:08:42,660
I dunno.

72
00:08:42,660 --> 00:08:46,540
There were a whole bunch of black things,
but they weren't roaches or mice.

73
00:08:59,680 --> 00:09:00,140
Well?

74
00:09:02,060 --> 00:09:03,850
I think they were dustbunnies.

75
00:09:04,270 --> 00:09:06,850
“Dustbunnies”?
Like in that picture book?

76
00:09:06,850 --> 00:09:10,400
That's right. Ghosts don't come out
on such nice days like this.

77
00:09:15,820 --> 00:09:18,200
When you're somewhere bright
and you suddenly walk into a dark room,

78
00:09:18,780 --> 00:09:21,700
dustbunnies appear while your eyes
are still adjusting to the darkness.

79
00:09:21,700 --> 00:09:22,830
Oh, I see.

80
00:09:23,450 --> 00:09:25,200
Dustbunnies, come out, come out, wherever you are!
Or else we'll give you the shock of your life!

81
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:36,880
Okay, let's get to work!

82
00:09:36,880 --> 00:09:39,890
Can you tell me where the stairs
to get to the top floor might be?

83
00:09:40,590 --> 00:09:41,390
Huh?

84
00:09:41,850 --> 00:09:44,430
Go find those stairs
and get the windows up there open.

85
00:09:44,930 --> 00:09:46,060
Okay!

86
00:09:46,060 --> 00:09:47,390
Hey, I'm coming too!

87
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:57,610
The toilet!

88
00:10:00,030 --> 00:10:01,070
Huh?!

89
00:10:04,030 --> 00:10:05,080
Huh?!

90
00:10:05,080 --> 00:10:06,290
Huh?!

91
00:10:09,540 --> 00:10:10,580
Huh?!

92
00:10:10,580 --> 00:10:11,710
Huh?!

93
00:10:14,000 --> 00:10:15,420
Ow!

94
00:10:15,420 --> 00:10:16,630
Huh?!

95
00:10:18,760 --> 00:10:19,590
Nothing!

96
00:10:20,470 --> 00:10:21,890
Nothing!

97
00:10:21,890 --> 00:10:23,600
Hey, that hurt!

98
00:10:31,770 --> 00:10:33,860
Mei, I found it!

99
00:10:40,570 --> 00:10:42,240
It's pitch black.

100
00:10:42,240 --> 00:10:43,870
It's the dustbunnies.

101
00:10:52,250 --> 00:10:53,420
An acorn.

102
00:11:43,090 --> 00:11:46,550
Are you there, Mr. Dustbunny?

103
00:12:08,450 --> 00:12:10,700
Okay…

104
00:12:10,700 --> 00:12:11,830
And lift…

105
00:12:12,410 --> 00:12:16,460
Dad, there's definitely something in this house!

106
00:12:16,460 --> 00:12:17,840
That's exciting.

107
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:22,460
Ever since I was a kid,
I've always wanted to live in a haunted house.

108
00:12:25,510 --> 00:12:26,760
That's not good!

109
00:13:12,180 --> 00:13:14,350
I got one! Sis!

110
00:13:28,160 --> 00:13:28,910
Mei.

111
00:13:39,710 --> 00:13:41,840
You sure are full of energy!

112
00:13:41,840 --> 00:13:45,050
This is our neighbor who's been looking after this place.
You can call her Granny.

113
00:13:45,050 --> 00:13:46,470
She's come to help us.

114
00:13:47,050 --> 00:13:50,390
Hello. I'm Satsuki and this is my sister, Mei.

115
00:13:50,390 --> 00:13:53,390
Hello to you, too.

116
00:13:53,390 --> 00:13:55,970
What a well-mannered girl you are!

117
00:13:55,970 --> 00:13:59,850
I'd have cleaned up the place
if I'd known you'd move in this early.

118
00:14:00,480 --> 00:14:02,520
No, you've done plenty.

119
00:14:02,520 --> 00:14:07,820
I've been so busy in the rice paddies lately,
but I've still been able to do a bit of dusting now and then.

120
00:14:09,110 --> 00:14:11,950
Mei, your hands are filthy.
What happened?

121
00:14:11,950 --> 00:14:14,330
The dustbunny got away.

122
00:14:14,330 --> 00:14:16,500
Ah! Your feet too!

123
00:14:20,420 --> 00:14:22,420
Hey, mine are black too!

124
00:14:24,710 --> 00:14:28,470
My, oh my, oh my.

125
00:14:31,390 --> 00:14:33,680
This must be the soot sprites coming out.

126
00:14:33,680 --> 00:14:35,260
“Soot sprites”?

127
00:14:35,260 --> 00:14:40,060
You mean something about this big
that scurry away in a noisy panic?

128
00:14:40,060 --> 00:14:40,560
That's right.

129
00:14:41,650 --> 00:14:44,900
They breed in empty old houses,

130
00:14:44,900 --> 00:14:48,570
running amok and covering them
with soot and dust.

131
00:14:49,700 --> 00:14:53,240
I could see them when I was little.

132
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:57,080
Oh, so I guess now you can too, huh?

133
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:59,120
Are they like goblins or something?

134
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:03,330
Nah, it's nothing scary like that.

135
00:15:03,330 --> 00:15:06,500
If you keep smiling, they won't bother you.

136
00:15:06,500 --> 00:15:08,760
And before you know it, they'll be long gone.

137
00:15:10,300 --> 00:15:14,300
I bet they're up in the ceiling right now,
talking about whether or not to move out.

138
00:15:20,350 --> 00:15:22,310
Mei, they're all gonna run away.

139
00:15:22,310 --> 00:15:23,350
That's no fun.

140
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:25,940
But what if a huge one comes out?

141
00:15:26,360 --> 00:15:27,650
I wouldn't be scared.

142
00:15:27,650 --> 00:15:31,650
Oh? Then I'm not gonna go with you
to the bathroom at night.

143
00:15:33,860 --> 00:15:36,580
All right, cleaning time.

144
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:39,160
Can you go and fetch some water
from the stream?

145
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:40,200
From the stream?

146
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,580
I'm coming too!

147
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:46,590
Mei, wait there, okay?

148
00:15:56,220 --> 00:15:57,930
Did you catch a fish?

149
00:16:09,820 --> 00:16:11,780
Granny, it's working!

150
00:16:12,190 --> 00:16:14,490
Keep pumping!

151
00:16:14,490 --> 00:16:16,780
Don't stop until the water gets cold.

152
00:16:16,780 --> 00:16:18,370
Okay!

153
00:17:00,410 --> 00:17:02,450
Oh, it's you again.

154
00:17:02,450 --> 00:17:03,410
Can I help you?

155
00:17:04,790 --> 00:17:07,420
M-My Mom… for Granny.

156
00:17:09,460 --> 00:17:10,670
What is it?

157
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,430
Hey, wait! What is this?

158
00:17:19,390 --> 00:17:21,050
Is that you, Kanta?

159
00:17:22,890 --> 00:17:28,230
Hey, you! Your house is haunted!

160
00:17:28,650 --> 00:17:29,730
Kanta!

161
00:17:40,030 --> 00:17:42,580
I remember doing the same sort of thing too.

162
00:17:43,160 --> 00:17:44,620
I hate boys.

163
00:17:44,620 --> 00:17:48,620
But I love your homemade rice cakes heaps,
Granny!

164
00:17:48,620 --> 00:17:50,460
Eat as much as you want.

165
00:17:51,380 --> 00:17:52,670
Thanks for your help!

166
00:17:55,840 --> 00:17:57,550
Thank you for everything.

167
00:19:15,840 --> 00:19:18,920
Dad, I think this wreck is gonna fall down.

168
00:19:21,130 --> 00:19:24,010
That wouldn't be good
since we've only just moved in.

169
00:19:59,130 --> 00:20:02,300
Let's all try laughing.
Then whatever scares you will go away.

170
00:20:04,590 --> 00:20:06,430
I'm not scared.

171
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,470
I'm not scared!

172
00:20:56,520 --> 00:20:58,060
That's it. Keep it going.

173
00:20:58,060 --> 00:20:59,110
Keep it going.

174
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:00,190
Keep it going.

175
00:21:05,490 --> 00:21:08,200
All right! The washing's finished!

176
00:21:17,790 --> 00:21:20,040
Here we go!

177
00:21:36,810 --> 00:21:39,150
Granny!

178
00:21:39,810 --> 00:21:42,020
Hello!

179
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:43,570
You sure are hard at work!

180
00:21:44,030 --> 00:21:46,280
Where're you all heading?

181
00:21:46,780 --> 00:21:49,530
We're going to visit Mom in the hospital!

182
00:21:49,530 --> 00:21:52,280
That's nice!

183
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:54,410
Say hello for me!

184
00:21:55,040 --> 00:21:56,500
We will!

185
00:22:12,850 --> 00:22:14,350
Ah! It's this way!

186
00:22:41,670 --> 00:22:42,460
Hello.

187
00:22:42,460 --> 00:22:43,920
Hello there.

188
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:46,920
Mom!

189
00:22:46,920 --> 00:22:49,510
Mei! I'm so glad you came.

190
00:22:49,510 --> 00:22:51,930
Dad took the wrong road.

191
00:22:51,930 --> 00:22:53,550
He did?

192
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:54,680
Thanks for coming.

193
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:56,640
Well, it's a school holiday
since it's a rice planting day.

194
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,100
Oh, I see.

195
00:22:58,100 --> 00:23:00,810
Dad's talking to the doctor.

196
00:23:00,810 --> 00:23:02,770
I'm so happy that you all came to see me.

197
00:23:03,310 --> 00:23:05,940
How's the new house?
Have you settled in okay?

198
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:13,160
Really? A haunted house?

199
00:23:13,160 --> 00:23:13,910
Yep.

200
00:23:14,280 --> 00:23:16,410
Do you like haunted houses, Mom?

201
00:23:16,410 --> 00:23:17,870
Of course I do!

202
00:23:17,870 --> 00:23:20,080
I can't wait to leave the hospital
and meet some ghosts.

203
00:23:20,080 --> 00:23:21,330
Isn't that great, Mei?

204
00:23:21,330 --> 00:23:22,540
Yeah!

205
00:23:22,540 --> 00:23:26,290
Mei was worried that you wouldn't like them.

206
00:23:26,290 --> 00:23:27,550
What about you two?

207
00:23:27,550 --> 00:23:28,460
I love them!

208
00:23:28,460 --> 00:23:30,420
I'm not scared of them!

209
00:23:32,720 --> 00:23:35,390
Are you fixing up Mei's hair, Satsuki?

210
00:23:35,390 --> 00:23:36,550
Yep.

211
00:23:36,550 --> 00:23:37,930
It's really good.

212
00:23:37,930 --> 00:23:39,100
Aren't you lucky, Mei?

213
00:23:40,520 --> 00:23:42,270
But she gets mad at me all the time.

214
00:23:42,690 --> 00:23:44,600
That's because you won't stay still.

215
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:46,610
Come here, Satsuki.

216
00:23:47,190 --> 00:23:49,110
Isn't yours too short?

217
00:23:49,110 --> 00:23:50,440
I like it this way.

218
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:52,450
What about me?! What about me?!

219
00:23:52,450 --> 00:23:53,360
Wait your turn!

220
00:23:53,990 --> 00:23:56,410
You still have such frizzy hair.

221
00:23:56,410 --> 00:23:58,910
It's just like mine when I was your age.

222
00:23:58,910 --> 00:24:02,870
Will it be like yours when I grow up?

223
00:24:03,290 --> 00:24:06,790
Probably, since you and I are a lot alike.

224
00:24:24,690 --> 00:24:26,730
Mom looked really well.

225
00:24:26,730 --> 00:24:30,610
You're right. The doctor says
she'll be able to leave the hospital soon.

226
00:24:31,190 --> 00:24:32,860
Soon? Like tomorrow?

227
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,360
There you go again with “tomorrow”.

228
00:24:35,360 --> 00:24:37,070
Tomorrow's probably a little too soon.

229
00:24:37,780 --> 00:24:40,830
Mom said she wants to sleep with me
in my bed.

230
00:24:40,830 --> 00:24:45,290
Oh? Weren't you saying
you're big enough to sleep alone now?

231
00:24:45,290 --> 00:24:47,210
Mom's special!

232
00:25:08,730 --> 00:25:10,400
Dad!

233
00:25:11,070 --> 00:25:12,480
It's morning!

234
00:25:16,240 --> 00:25:18,530
Wake up!

235
00:25:24,040 --> 00:25:25,790
Sorry, I overslept again.

236
00:25:25,790 --> 00:25:27,750
I've got to pack my own lunch from today.

237
00:25:28,120 --> 00:25:30,130
Oops, I totally forgot about that.

238
00:25:30,590 --> 00:25:33,250
It's all right.
I've made something for all of us.

239
00:25:33,250 --> 00:25:34,170
It's burning!

240
00:25:34,170 --> 00:25:35,050
I'll be there in a sec!

241
00:25:38,010 --> 00:25:39,720
This one's yours, Mei.

242
00:25:40,550 --> 00:25:42,140
That's my one?!

243
00:25:43,010 --> 00:25:44,560
Mei, sit down and eat!

244
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:45,430
Here you go!

245
00:25:46,940 --> 00:25:48,980
Put the lid on yourself, okay?

246
00:25:52,020 --> 00:25:54,780
Satsuki!

247
00:25:54,780 --> 00:25:56,320
Uh-oh.

248
00:25:56,320 --> 00:25:58,990
I'm here!

249
00:26:00,620 --> 00:26:02,410
You made a friend already?

250
00:26:02,410 --> 00:26:04,490
'Cause she's shouting, “Satsuki!”

251
00:26:04,870 --> 00:26:06,450
Yup, that's Michiko.

252
00:26:08,830 --> 00:26:09,540
I'm done!

253
00:26:11,880 --> 00:26:13,800
See ya later!

254
00:26:17,220 --> 00:26:18,380
Morning!

255
00:26:18,380 --> 00:26:20,010
Morning. We better get going!

256
00:26:20,010 --> 00:26:20,680
Yeah.

257
00:26:21,760 --> 00:26:22,430
Hi-ya!

258
00:26:22,430 --> 00:26:23,720
Morning!

259
00:26:32,810 --> 00:26:34,320
Dad!

260
00:26:35,480 --> 00:26:37,280
Do I look like a big girl?

261
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:39,650
Yep. Now where are you off to
with your lunch bag?

262
00:26:39,650 --> 00:26:41,320
Just a little over thataway.

263
00:27:03,760 --> 00:27:06,010
Dad, is it lunchtime yet?

264
00:27:06,010 --> 00:27:07,970
Huh? Already?

265
00:27:20,360 --> 00:27:22,700
You be the flower shop, Dad.

266
00:27:39,050 --> 00:27:40,470
Pole-tads!

267
00:27:58,980 --> 00:28:01,570
Huh? It's got no bottom.

268
00:28:15,000 --> 00:28:16,330
Gotcha!

269
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:56,010
Who are you? A dustbunny?

270
00:34:24,120 --> 00:34:27,200
Totoro? Your name's Totoro, isn't it?

271
00:34:32,290 --> 00:34:34,250
Yep, you're Totoro for sure.

272
00:34:37,090 --> 00:34:38,220
Totoro.

273
00:35:46,580 --> 00:35:47,330
See ya!

274
00:35:47,330 --> 00:35:48,410
See you later!

275
00:35:50,910 --> 00:35:51,790
I'm home!

276
00:35:51,790 --> 00:35:52,750
Welcome back.

277
00:35:52,750 --> 00:35:54,630
Oh, is it this late already?

278
00:35:54,630 --> 00:35:56,750
Where's Mei? I'm off to Michiko's.

279
00:35:56,750 --> 00:35:58,380
We haven't even had lunch yet.

280
00:35:58,380 --> 00:36:00,090
Isn't Mei playing in the garden?

281
00:36:00,090 --> 00:36:00,840
Mei!

282
00:36:02,470 --> 00:36:03,970
Mei!

283
00:36:05,430 --> 00:36:06,470
Mei!

284
00:36:09,680 --> 00:36:10,770
Mei!

285
00:36:17,310 --> 00:36:20,990
Dad, I found her hat!

286
00:36:36,380 --> 00:36:38,000
Mei. Mei.

287
00:36:45,380 --> 00:36:47,850
Mei! Come on, wake up!

288
00:36:49,350 --> 00:36:51,560
What do you think you're doing
sleeping out here?!

289
00:36:53,480 --> 00:36:54,770
Where's Totoro?

290
00:36:54,770 --> 00:36:56,100
Totoro?

291
00:36:56,100 --> 00:36:58,360
Huh? Where'd he…?

292
00:37:00,980 --> 00:37:02,940
Were you dreaming?

293
00:37:02,940 --> 00:37:04,400
Totoro was here.

294
00:37:04,780 --> 00:37:07,620
“Totoro”? Don't you mean a troll,
like in your picture book?

295
00:37:07,990 --> 00:37:11,200
Yeah, but he said Totoro for sure.

296
00:37:11,200 --> 00:37:15,080
He was all furry and had a huge mouth like this.

297
00:37:15,080 --> 00:37:21,840
There was a little one, a bigger one,
and a huge one like this that was sleeping.

298
00:37:25,630 --> 00:37:27,300
There you are.

299
00:37:27,300 --> 00:37:29,090
Wow, this is amazing.

300
00:37:29,850 --> 00:37:31,390
This'd make a great secret hiding place.

301
00:37:31,390 --> 00:37:34,810
Dad, Mei said that she met Totoro here.

302
00:37:34,810 --> 00:37:35,600
Totoro?

303
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:36,230
Yeah.

304
00:37:36,640 --> 00:37:37,730
This way!

305
00:37:46,110 --> 00:37:47,910
Hey, wait up!

306
00:37:49,740 --> 00:37:50,700
Huh?

307
00:37:53,410 --> 00:37:54,540
Here?

308
00:37:54,540 --> 00:37:55,870
Nope.

309
00:37:56,250 --> 00:37:58,670
Last time, it went to a big tree.

310
00:37:58,670 --> 00:38:00,670
But there wasn't any other path.

311
00:38:01,380 --> 00:38:04,380
Ah, Mei! Come back!

312
00:38:04,380 --> 00:38:06,380
Mei, I said come back!

313
00:38:18,770 --> 00:38:23,270
But it's true! Totoro was really here!

314
00:38:23,270 --> 00:38:24,530
I'm not lying.

315
00:38:33,870 --> 00:38:34,660
Mei?

316
00:38:35,580 --> 00:38:37,040
I'm not lying.

317
00:38:38,790 --> 00:38:42,540
Satsuki and I don't think you're lying.

318
00:38:43,040 --> 00:38:46,550
You must've met the guardian of this forest.

319
00:38:46,550 --> 00:38:48,510
You were very lucky.

320
00:38:49,260 --> 00:38:51,760
But you won't always be able to see him.

321
00:38:53,720 --> 00:38:56,100
All right, we should give him a proper greeting.

322
00:38:56,100 --> 00:38:57,100
A greeting?

323
00:38:57,100 --> 00:38:58,810
To Tsukamori Forest we go!

324
00:39:15,330 --> 00:39:16,790
Whew!

325
00:39:16,790 --> 00:39:18,370
You're getting heavy, Mei…

326
00:39:18,370 --> 00:39:20,120
Dad, it's that camphor tree!

327
00:39:21,330 --> 00:39:22,500
It's big, isn't it?

328
00:39:30,760 --> 00:39:31,550
This is it!

329
00:39:33,010 --> 00:39:33,760
This is the tree?

330
00:39:33,760 --> 00:39:34,430
Yep.

331
00:39:35,140 --> 00:39:37,510
Come on, Dad! Hurry up!

332
00:39:48,440 --> 00:39:50,490
The hole's gone.

333
00:39:50,490 --> 00:39:51,780
Are you sure it was here?

334
00:39:51,780 --> 00:39:52,570
Yeah.

335
00:39:53,610 --> 00:39:55,490
She said the hole's disappeared.

336
00:39:55,490 --> 00:39:58,080
See? I told you that you won't be able
to see him whenever you want.

337
00:39:58,080 --> 00:39:59,540
But will we see him again?

338
00:39:59,540 --> 00:40:00,870
I want to meet him too.

339
00:40:01,750 --> 00:40:04,210
If you're lucky, sure.

340
00:40:05,790 --> 00:40:07,540
What a magnificent tree.

341
00:40:09,130 --> 00:40:13,430
This tree must've stood here
for years and years.

342
00:40:14,590 --> 00:40:18,600
You know, trees and people
used to be good friends long ago.

343
00:40:19,850 --> 00:40:24,190
When I saw that tree,
I fell in love with this place.

344
00:40:24,190 --> 00:40:26,980
And I know Mom will like it too.

345
00:40:26,980 --> 00:40:30,320
Okay, let's pay our respects
and then get back home for lunch.

346
00:40:30,320 --> 00:40:32,990
Oh, that's right! I promised
to go over to Michiko's place.

347
00:40:32,990 --> 00:40:34,740
I want to go too!

348
00:40:34,740 --> 00:40:35,660
Attention!

349
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:38,370
We thank you for looking after Mei.

350
00:40:38,370 --> 00:40:40,950
And we ask that you please continue
to look after us.

351
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:45,170
And the race home is on!

352
00:40:45,170 --> 00:40:46,210
Hey! That's not fair!

353
00:40:46,210 --> 00:40:46,790
Hey!

354
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:49,290
Wait up!

355
00:40:51,090 --> 00:40:53,010
Hurry up!

356
00:40:53,010 --> 00:40:54,880
Wait up!

357
00:40:57,340 --> 00:40:59,970
“I've got some really amazing news for you today.

358
00:41:00,640 --> 00:41:03,640
Mei met the giant creature, Totoro.

359
00:41:09,060 --> 00:41:13,150
I'm really hoping to meet him myself, too.”

360
00:41:43,720 --> 00:41:46,980
Kanta, you're going to be late
if you don't hurry it up!

361
00:41:46,980 --> 00:41:47,940
Yeah.

362
00:42:11,420 --> 00:42:12,090
Ahem!

363
00:42:30,690 --> 00:42:31,900
Mei?

364
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:33,610
Miss!

365
00:42:33,610 --> 00:42:34,900
Yes, Satsuki?

366
00:42:35,690 --> 00:42:37,400
Um, it's my sister.

367
00:42:44,580 --> 00:42:46,410
Granny. Mei.

368
00:42:46,410 --> 00:42:50,960
I'm sorry. She insisted to be with you
and wouldn't listen to me.

369
00:42:51,500 --> 00:42:52,790
But…

370
00:42:52,790 --> 00:42:56,050
Mei, it's Dad's day at the university,

371
00:42:56,050 --> 00:42:59,050
so you promised to be a good girl
and wait at Granny's today.

372
00:43:02,010 --> 00:43:06,310
I still have two hours of school,
and Granny's too busy for this.

373
00:43:06,680 --> 00:43:11,310
She's been so good up 'til now, weren't you?

374
00:43:19,070 --> 00:43:21,240
Granny, I'll go talk to my teacher.

375
00:43:27,330 --> 00:43:32,040
Satsuki's family are going through a tough time
because their mom is in hospital.

376
00:43:32,040 --> 00:43:34,330
So everyone, I want you to be nice to them.

377
00:43:41,680 --> 00:43:43,260
What's that?

378
00:43:43,260 --> 00:43:44,510
It's Totoro.

379
00:43:46,180 --> 00:43:48,180
You're supposed to be quiet, okay?

380
00:43:48,180 --> 00:43:48,970
Okay.

381
00:43:56,230 --> 00:43:57,150
See you later!

382
00:43:57,150 --> 00:43:58,070
See you later!

383
00:43:58,070 --> 00:43:59,230
I'm going now!

384
00:43:59,610 --> 00:44:01,570
Bye-bye, Mei!

385
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:04,160
Tell everyone I had to
give the club a miss today.

386
00:44:04,160 --> 00:44:06,160
Okay, we'll let the teacher know.

387
00:44:06,160 --> 00:44:07,410
See you later!

388
00:44:07,410 --> 00:44:08,370
Bye-bye!

389
00:44:09,450 --> 00:44:11,290
We'd better get a move on, Mei.
It's gonna rain.

390
00:44:11,290 --> 00:44:12,080
Okay.

391
00:44:20,130 --> 00:44:21,550
Ah! Here it comes!

392
00:44:33,890 --> 00:44:34,520
Come on.

393
00:44:38,690 --> 00:44:41,070
I didn't cry. Aren't I good?

394
00:44:41,070 --> 00:44:41,740
Yeah…

395
00:44:43,700 --> 00:44:45,910
But this isn't good.

396
00:44:48,410 --> 00:44:51,540
Dear Lord Guardian, please let us
shelter here for a little while.

397
00:45:35,460 --> 00:45:36,330
But…

398
00:45:57,020 --> 00:45:58,900
That was lucky, wasn't it, Sis?

399
00:45:58,900 --> 00:45:59,440
Yeah.

400
00:46:00,230 --> 00:46:02,230
This umbrella's got holes in it.

401
00:46:14,080 --> 00:46:16,580
Looks like Dad didn't take his umbrella.

402
00:46:16,580 --> 00:46:18,170
I'm gonna go too.

403
00:46:21,630 --> 00:46:23,550
I said I forgot it!

404
00:46:23,550 --> 00:46:27,340
What idiot forgets his umbrella
on a rainy day?

405
00:46:27,340 --> 00:46:28,800
That hurt!

406
00:46:28,800 --> 00:46:31,350
I bet you were swinging it around
and it broke.

407
00:46:31,350 --> 00:46:32,510
I did not!

408
00:46:45,980 --> 00:46:47,320
Hello?

409
00:46:49,610 --> 00:46:51,950
Oh, Satsuki, and Mei too.

410
00:46:51,950 --> 00:46:53,330
Grandma!

411
00:46:54,790 --> 00:46:56,370
I'm sorry about today.

412
00:46:56,370 --> 00:46:58,250
Not at all.
I'm sorry we couldn't do more.

413
00:46:58,710 --> 00:47:01,920
Um, Kanta lent us this umbrella.

414
00:47:01,920 --> 00:47:04,130
Huh? He did?

415
00:47:04,130 --> 00:47:05,590
It's a bit worse for wear, isn't it?

416
00:47:06,050 --> 00:47:08,340
Mei was with me, so it was a big help.

417
00:47:08,340 --> 00:47:10,680
But Kanta must've got soaked.

418
00:47:10,680 --> 00:47:11,970
Thank you for everything.

419
00:47:12,340 --> 00:47:16,970
Not at all. He gets himself covered in mud all the time,
so it probably cleaned him up a little.

420
00:47:17,600 --> 00:47:19,100
Are you off to meet your dad?

421
00:47:19,100 --> 00:47:19,770
Yes.

422
00:47:19,770 --> 00:47:21,270
What good girls you are.

423
00:47:21,770 --> 00:47:23,310
Bye-bye, Mei.

424
00:47:23,310 --> 00:47:24,360
Bye-bye.

425
00:47:34,740 --> 00:47:36,580
Who was that?

426
00:47:36,580 --> 00:47:37,540
Beats me!

427
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:43,710
Just in time!

428
00:47:57,060 --> 00:47:58,270
Are you getting on?

429
00:47:59,720 --> 00:48:01,520
All right, drive on.

430
00:48:09,820 --> 00:48:12,150
Dad wasn't on it.

431
00:48:12,150 --> 00:48:14,240
He'll be on the next one for sure.

432
00:48:14,240 --> 00:48:16,160
Do you want to wait at Granny's?

433
00:48:52,440 --> 00:48:53,570
What's the matter?

434
00:49:25,350 --> 00:49:26,560
Mei?

435
00:49:27,400 --> 00:49:28,610
Are you sleepy?

436
00:49:29,480 --> 00:49:31,400
That's why I told you…

437
00:49:31,400 --> 00:49:33,240
Do you want to go to Granny's now?

438
00:49:35,530 --> 00:49:37,320
It won't be much longer,
so hang in there.

439
00:49:43,750 --> 00:49:46,330
The bus sure is late.

440
00:49:54,010 --> 00:49:54,760
Here.

441
00:51:18,720 --> 00:51:19,720
Totoro?

442
00:51:29,930 --> 00:51:31,600
Oh, just a second.

443
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:38,440
You can borrow this.

444
00:51:40,030 --> 00:51:42,110
Quick, Mei's slipping off.

445
00:51:48,580 --> 00:51:50,120
You hold it like this.

446
00:53:07,200 --> 00:53:08,320
Here comes the bus!

447
00:54:15,930 --> 00:54:19,100
He took Dad's umbrella…

448
00:54:32,700 --> 00:54:34,330
I'm sorry.

449
00:54:34,330 --> 00:54:35,290
All right, drive on.

450
00:54:36,120 --> 00:54:39,170
The train was late, so I missed the bus.

451
00:54:40,000 --> 00:54:41,380
Were you worried?

452
00:54:42,170 --> 00:54:44,500
He came out, Dad! He really came out!

453
00:54:44,500 --> 00:54:46,170
And a cat bus!

454
00:54:46,670 --> 00:54:47,670
Huh?

455
00:54:48,090 --> 00:54:49,880
It was huge!

456
00:54:49,880 --> 00:54:51,890
With eyes like this!

457
00:54:54,810 --> 00:54:59,390
I met him! I met Totoro!

458
00:54:59,390 --> 00:55:01,480
It was so cool!

459
00:55:12,660 --> 00:55:13,490
Come on!

460
00:55:22,080 --> 00:55:25,920
“Dear Mom, my heart's still racing
from the excitement today.

461
00:55:25,920 --> 00:55:30,010
It was such a mysterious, weird and fun day.

462
00:55:30,010 --> 00:55:33,430
Totoro even gave us a wonderful present.

463
00:55:33,430 --> 00:55:37,930
It was wrapped in a bamboo leaf
and tied up with dragon whiskers.

464
00:55:37,930 --> 00:55:40,600
We opened it when we got home…

465
00:55:40,600 --> 00:55:42,940
and found lots of nuts inside.”

466
00:55:47,650 --> 00:55:50,530
“We thought our garden would be even better
if it turned into a forest,

467
00:55:50,530 --> 00:55:52,990
so we planted them in the garden.

468
00:55:52,990 --> 00:55:53,780
But…”

469
00:55:53,780 --> 00:55:55,780
“…they don't want to sprout.

470
00:55:55,780 --> 00:56:00,330
Mei's there all day, every day,
and keeps saying, ‘Still nothing. Still nothing.’

471
00:56:01,540 --> 00:56:05,170
She looks just like a patient little crab.

472
00:56:10,340 --> 00:56:12,260
It's nearly summer vacation.

473
00:56:12,260 --> 00:56:16,550
Dearest, dear Mom, please get well soon.
Love, Satsuki.”

474
00:56:20,060 --> 00:56:21,140
Hey, come on.

475
00:56:26,020 --> 00:56:26,900
Lights out.

476
00:56:26,900 --> 00:56:28,400
Hang on!

477
00:56:28,860 --> 00:56:31,610
Dad, do you think they'll sprout tomorrow?

478
00:56:31,990 --> 00:56:35,870
Hmm, well I'm sure Totoro would know.

479
00:56:35,870 --> 00:56:36,950
Good night.

480
00:57:26,000 --> 00:57:26,750
Mei!

481
00:57:45,270 --> 00:57:47,270
That's where we planted the nuts.

482
00:59:19,490 --> 00:59:21,360
We did it!

483
01:00:37,320 --> 01:00:40,280
Mei, we're the wind!

484
01:01:40,880 --> 01:01:42,300
The tree's gone.

485
01:01:47,430 --> 01:01:49,100
We did it!

486
01:01:52,470 --> 01:01:53,460
It was a dream!

487
01:01:53,460 --> 01:01:54,930
But it wasn't a dream!

488
01:01:54,930 --> 01:01:55,940
It was a dream!

489
01:01:55,940 --> 01:01:57,270
But it wasn't a dream!

490
01:01:57,270 --> 01:01:59,310
We did it! We did it!

491
01:01:59,310 --> 01:02:00,400
We did it!

492
01:02:16,960 --> 01:02:19,880
Mr. Kusakabe! Telegram!

493
01:02:21,090 --> 01:02:22,460
Mr. Kusakabe!

494
01:02:23,590 --> 01:02:25,340
You've got a telegram!

495
01:02:26,920 --> 01:02:28,300
No one's home?

496
01:02:35,430 --> 01:02:37,560
Granny!

497
01:02:41,860 --> 01:02:43,320
I'm over here.

498
01:02:45,230 --> 01:02:47,320
This one's ready to eat.

499
01:02:56,540 --> 01:02:58,080
What about this one, Granny?

500
01:02:58,080 --> 01:02:59,250
Go for it.

501
01:03:05,800 --> 01:03:08,880
Your garden's like a house of treasures, Granny.

502
01:03:09,590 --> 01:03:12,010
Well, let's take a little break.

503
01:03:18,060 --> 01:03:20,810
Right, these are nice and cold now.

504
01:03:21,230 --> 01:03:22,810
Snack time!

505
01:03:32,370 --> 01:03:33,700
It's good!

506
01:03:33,700 --> 01:03:35,120
You think?

507
01:03:35,120 --> 01:03:39,580
Well, they've been soaking up the sun,
so they're good for you.

508
01:03:39,960 --> 01:03:41,330
Would they help Mom get better too?

509
01:03:41,960 --> 01:03:43,420
Of course.

510
01:03:43,420 --> 01:03:46,920
If she eats my homegrown veggies,
she'll get better in no time.

511
01:03:47,340 --> 01:03:50,090
Mom's coming home this Saturday.

512
01:03:50,090 --> 01:03:52,130
She's gonna sleep with me in my bed!

513
01:03:52,840 --> 01:03:55,600
I see. So she'll finally be out of the hospital.

514
01:03:55,600 --> 01:04:00,770
Nah, it's a temporary thing so she can
get used to the outdoors little by little.

515
01:04:00,770 --> 01:04:02,100
So she has to go back on Monday.

516
01:04:02,560 --> 01:04:04,190
Oh, okay.

517
01:04:04,190 --> 01:04:06,860
Then we'll feed her lots of my veggies
while she's here.

518
01:04:06,860 --> 01:04:10,610
I'll give her this corn I picked.

519
01:04:10,610 --> 01:04:12,410
I'm sure that'll make her very happy.

520
01:04:12,860 --> 01:04:13,780
Yeah!

521
01:04:21,910 --> 01:04:24,170
A telegram. We accepted it
since you weren't home.

522
01:04:24,170 --> 01:04:25,040
For us?

523
01:04:29,260 --> 01:04:31,630
Granny, Dad won't be back
until later this evening.

524
01:04:32,130 --> 01:04:34,590
Then you better open it, just in case it's urgent.

525
01:04:38,350 --> 01:04:42,350
Please contact Shichikokuyama.

526
01:04:42,730 --> 01:04:45,900
Shichikokuyama Hospital!
It's from Mom's hospital!

527
01:04:45,900 --> 01:04:47,860
Maybe something happened to her.

528
01:04:50,030 --> 01:04:52,280
What should I do, Granny?
They want us to contact them.

529
01:04:52,280 --> 01:04:54,160
All right, calm down.

530
01:04:54,160 --> 01:04:56,450
Do you know where your dad is?

531
01:04:56,450 --> 01:04:59,830
I know his office number at the university,
but we don't have a phone.

532
01:04:59,830 --> 01:05:04,210
Kanta, take her back to the main house
and let her use our phone.

533
01:05:04,210 --> 01:05:04,920
Okay.

534
01:05:09,210 --> 01:05:11,840
Mei, stay here!

535
01:05:21,310 --> 01:05:23,180
Mei, you need to stay with Granny!

536
01:06:00,760 --> 01:06:03,100
Hello, I'd like to make
a long-distance call, please.

537
01:06:04,350 --> 01:06:08,230
It's to Tokyo 31-1382.

538
01:06:08,230 --> 01:06:08,940
Yes.

539
01:06:10,520 --> 01:06:13,440
What an adorable girl, Kanta.

540
01:06:16,030 --> 01:06:17,400
Hello?

541
01:06:17,400 --> 01:06:18,070
Okay.

542
01:06:19,660 --> 01:06:22,030
Hello, is this the archaeology department?

543
01:06:22,030 --> 01:06:24,450
Could I speak to my father—
I mean, Mr. Kusakabe.

544
01:06:25,370 --> 01:06:27,250
I'm Satsuki Kusakabe.

545
01:06:27,250 --> 01:06:27,790
Yes.

546
01:06:31,340 --> 01:06:33,250
Dad? It's me, Satsuki!

547
01:06:33,630 --> 01:06:34,880
Oh, what's up?

548
01:06:38,300 --> 01:06:39,260
From the hospital?

549
01:06:39,260 --> 01:06:42,350
Okay, I'll call them right away.

550
01:06:42,350 --> 01:06:43,890
Did something happen to her?

551
01:06:43,890 --> 01:06:45,310
What are we gonna do, Dad?

552
01:06:45,310 --> 01:06:46,560
Don't worry.

553
01:06:46,560 --> 01:06:49,730
I'll call the hospital
and then call you right back.

554
01:06:49,730 --> 01:06:51,520
So just wait there.

555
01:06:53,270 --> 01:06:54,860
Well, I'm hanging up now, okay?

556
01:06:57,320 --> 01:06:59,610
Ma'am, could I please wait here?

557
01:06:59,610 --> 01:07:00,860
My dad's going to call me back.

558
01:07:01,370 --> 01:07:03,620
Sure, stay as long as you like.

559
01:07:11,080 --> 01:07:12,840
Sis!

560
01:07:21,760 --> 01:07:24,760
No you don't! This corn's for my mom!

561
01:07:26,430 --> 01:07:29,600
I said no, I'm giving it to my mom!

562
01:07:45,910 --> 01:07:48,870
Mei, they said Mom's not doing so well,

563
01:07:49,410 --> 01:07:51,830
so she can't come home this weekend.

564
01:07:52,500 --> 01:07:53,580
No!

565
01:07:54,920 --> 01:07:56,210
There's nothing we can do.

566
01:07:56,210 --> 01:07:58,460
You don't want her to overdo it
and get worse, do you?

567
01:07:58,840 --> 01:08:00,470
No!

568
01:08:01,680 --> 01:08:03,720
Come on, we just have to wait a little longer.

569
01:08:03,720 --> 01:08:05,720
No!

570
01:08:06,890 --> 01:08:08,970
So you don't care if she dies, do you?!

571
01:08:09,350 --> 01:08:10,980
No!

572
01:08:11,640 --> 01:08:12,480
You're so stupid!

573
01:08:12,900 --> 01:08:13,940
I've had it with you!

574
01:08:25,160 --> 01:08:26,030
We should go.

575
01:08:29,700 --> 01:08:33,170
She's so stupid!

576
01:08:37,920 --> 01:08:41,050
So stupid…

577
01:08:59,690 --> 01:09:03,360
It's about time we put away the laundry.

578
01:09:03,990 --> 01:09:07,120
Don't be sad.

579
01:09:07,120 --> 01:09:10,950
Granny's here to help, so cheer up.

580
01:09:15,000 --> 01:09:19,130
Your dad said he'll stop by the hospital.

581
01:09:19,840 --> 01:09:22,630
Besides, they said it's just a cold,

582
01:09:23,010 --> 01:09:26,390
so she'll be home next Saturday.

583
01:09:30,970 --> 01:09:34,770
This is just like last time when they said
she wouldn't be in hospital for long.

584
01:09:35,810 --> 01:09:37,350
They said it was just like a cold.

585
01:09:39,020 --> 01:09:40,860
But what if she dies?

586
01:09:40,860 --> 01:09:42,860
Satsuki…

587
01:09:43,490 --> 01:09:45,280
Maybe Mom's…

588
01:09:49,280 --> 01:09:52,290
Don't worry, it'll be okay.

589
01:09:52,290 --> 01:09:56,210
Nobody would ever leave
such sweet girls like you.

590
01:09:57,170 --> 01:10:00,920
There, there. Don't cry.

591
01:10:00,920 --> 01:10:05,720
I'll stay here until Dad comes back, okay?

592
01:10:47,340 --> 01:10:50,760
Mei!

593
01:10:55,060 --> 01:10:56,770
Mei!

594
01:11:00,100 --> 01:11:01,900
Mei!

595
01:11:05,070 --> 01:11:06,320
Did she come back?

596
01:11:06,320 --> 01:11:08,530
Wasn't she at the bus stop?

597
01:11:08,530 --> 01:11:09,280
No.

598
01:11:10,160 --> 01:11:13,200
That's strange.
Where could she have gone?

599
01:11:13,700 --> 01:11:15,790
I had a big fight with her earlier.

600
01:11:15,790 --> 01:11:17,540
I mean, she was…

601
01:11:17,540 --> 01:11:20,210
Maybe she's heading to the hospital!

602
01:11:20,210 --> 01:11:23,090
Shichikokuyama Hospital?

603
01:11:23,090 --> 01:11:26,420
Why, that's a three-hour walk
even for grown-ups!

604
01:11:26,420 --> 01:11:27,210
I'll go check!

605
01:11:28,880 --> 01:11:30,010
Kanta!

606
01:11:30,470 --> 01:11:33,390
Quick! Go get your dad!

607
01:11:33,390 --> 01:11:35,890
Mei's missing!

608
01:11:44,730 --> 01:11:47,730
She's so silly—always getting lost.

609
01:11:55,410 --> 01:11:57,700
Mei!

610
01:12:04,670 --> 01:12:06,670
Excuse me, mister. Um…

611
01:12:07,750 --> 01:12:08,630
Huh?

612
01:12:08,630 --> 01:12:13,220
Have you seen a little girl pass this way?
She's my sister.

613
01:12:13,220 --> 01:12:15,680
Let's see… A little girl?

614
01:12:16,100 --> 01:12:18,350
I'm pretty sure
I would've noticed someone like that.

615
01:12:19,600 --> 01:12:21,180
Maybe she wasn't here.

616
01:12:40,700 --> 01:12:42,960
Are you sure she came this way?

617
01:12:42,960 --> 01:12:44,080
I don't know.

618
01:12:52,930 --> 01:12:55,430
Mei!

619
01:13:16,410 --> 01:13:18,740
Please stop!

620
01:13:20,740 --> 01:13:22,160
That was reckless, you idiot!

621
01:13:22,160 --> 01:13:25,000
I'm looking for my sister.
Have you seen a little girl?

622
01:13:26,000 --> 01:13:26,880
Your little sister?

623
01:13:27,330 --> 01:13:30,880
I think she's heading to Shichikokuyama Hospital.
She's only four years old.

624
01:13:31,510 --> 01:13:32,920
Did you see anyone, Yoko?

625
01:13:32,920 --> 01:13:38,390
No. We just came from there,
but we didn't see anyone like that.

626
01:13:39,510 --> 01:13:41,260
Really? Thanks anyway.

627
01:13:42,390 --> 01:13:44,180
Where have you come from?

628
01:13:44,180 --> 01:13:45,350
From Matsugo.

629
01:13:45,350 --> 01:13:46,610
Matsugo?!

630
01:13:46,610 --> 01:13:48,770
Surely she can't have come this far?

631
01:13:50,230 --> 01:13:51,190
Well, bye.

632
01:14:02,830 --> 01:14:04,450
Satsuki!

633
01:14:06,040 --> 01:14:08,250
Kanta!

634
01:14:09,330 --> 01:14:10,000
Find her?

635
01:14:10,000 --> 01:14:11,420
No. And you?

636
01:14:11,420 --> 01:14:12,500
No.

637
01:14:12,500 --> 01:14:14,760
My dad and some others are looking for her.

638
01:14:14,760 --> 01:14:17,010
I'll go to Shichikokuyama for you,

639
01:14:17,010 --> 01:14:18,840
so you should go back home.

640
01:14:18,840 --> 01:14:22,760
She must've taken a wrong turn
on the way to the hospital.

641
01:14:23,220 --> 01:14:26,020
A little while ago,
they found a sandal by the pond.

642
01:14:33,280 --> 01:14:36,030
We're not sure if it's hers or not!

643
01:14:53,250 --> 01:14:54,550
Did you find her?

644
01:15:26,330 --> 01:15:27,290
Lord have mercy on her.

645
01:15:27,290 --> 01:15:28,290
Lord have mercy on her.

646
01:15:28,290 --> 01:15:29,710
Lord have mercy on her.

647
01:15:29,710 --> 01:15:30,580
Lord have mercy on her.

648
01:15:30,960 --> 01:15:33,590
The mud's too deep around there,
better search further away!

649
01:15:33,590 --> 01:15:35,590
Hey, are there any more poles?

650
01:15:44,430 --> 01:15:46,640
Grandma, Satsuki's here!

651
01:15:51,310 --> 01:15:52,850
Granny!

652
01:15:54,150 --> 01:15:55,940
I-It's hers, isn't it?

653
01:16:05,280 --> 01:16:06,200
It's not Mei's.

654
01:16:17,130 --> 01:16:19,170
Thank goodness.

655
01:16:19,170 --> 01:16:22,720
I was sure it was Mei-chan's.

656
01:16:22,720 --> 01:16:25,800
What's that? Granny was just
jumping to conclusions?

657
01:16:27,390 --> 01:16:29,140
Then, uh, where's she gone?

658
01:16:29,140 --> 01:16:30,930
I s'pose we'll start searchin'
all over the place again.

659
01:16:30,930 --> 01:16:32,640
We better hurry, it'll be dark soon.

660
01:16:32,640 --> 01:16:36,480
Sorry, everyone. I know it's a lot to ask,
but we'll have to split up.

661
01:16:36,480 --> 01:16:37,900
It's fine. We're all in this together!

662
01:16:37,900 --> 01:16:39,940
Shouldn't someone notify the police?

663
01:16:39,940 --> 01:16:40,490
Okay, let's do that.

664
01:17:06,550 --> 01:17:07,680
Please,

665
01:17:07,680 --> 01:17:09,720
let me in to Totoro's home.

666
01:17:09,720 --> 01:17:11,560
Mei's missing.

667
01:17:11,560 --> 01:17:15,520
It's almost dark, and she's out there all alone.

668
01:17:46,430 --> 01:17:47,390
Totoro!

669
01:17:49,470 --> 01:17:53,430
Mei's missing, Totoro. We looked everywhere,
but we couldn't find her.

670
01:17:53,930 --> 01:17:56,230
Please help me find her!

671
01:17:57,150 --> 01:17:59,440
I'm sure by now she's crying somewhere.

672
01:18:00,730 --> 01:18:02,940
I don't know what else to do.

673
01:19:01,880 --> 01:19:03,550
No one else can see it.

674
01:20:14,870 --> 01:20:19,500
Mei!

675
01:20:27,170 --> 01:20:28,590
The trees are moving out of the way!

676
01:21:00,370 --> 01:21:01,830
Mei!

677
01:21:05,830 --> 01:21:08,040
Sis!

678
01:21:09,920 --> 01:21:11,800
Sis!

679
01:21:11,800 --> 01:21:13,130
Mei!

680
01:21:22,810 --> 01:21:23,850
Mei!

681
01:21:23,850 --> 01:21:25,770
Sis!

682
01:21:28,860 --> 01:21:29,770
You silly girl.

683
01:21:29,770 --> 01:21:31,480
I'm sorry.

684
01:21:34,070 --> 01:21:37,160
Did you want to give your corn to Mom?

685
01:21:49,460 --> 01:21:50,750
You'll take us to the hospital?

686
01:21:53,880 --> 01:21:55,130
Thank you!

687
01:22:04,430 --> 01:22:09,060
I'm sorry. The hospital didn't need
to send a telegram just for a cold.

688
01:22:09,560 --> 01:22:12,320
The girls must be worried.

689
01:22:12,320 --> 01:22:13,820
I feel so bad about it all.

690
01:22:14,190 --> 01:22:16,950
No, they'll be fine
once they know what's going on.

691
01:22:16,950 --> 01:22:20,120
You and the girls have all been doing so well
holding out this long.

692
01:22:20,120 --> 01:22:21,950
The good times will be
just around the corner.

693
01:22:23,660 --> 01:22:27,210
I think it's been harder on the girls
than they let on.

694
01:22:27,210 --> 01:22:30,210
I'm especially sorry for Satsuki
because she's been so understanding.

695
01:22:31,340 --> 01:22:32,460
You're right.

696
01:22:33,250 --> 01:22:37,430
Once I'm out of the hospital,
I'm going to spoil those girls rotten.

697
01:22:37,430 --> 01:22:38,300
Oh no!

698
01:22:45,810 --> 01:22:47,810
Mom's laughing.

699
01:22:47,810 --> 01:22:49,190
Looks like she's fine.

700
01:22:49,190 --> 01:22:49,980
Yeah.

701
01:22:57,900 --> 01:23:00,370
Okay, I have to hurry up and get well!

702
01:23:00,370 --> 01:23:01,120
Yeah.

703
01:23:02,450 --> 01:23:03,240
Huh?

704
01:23:09,960 --> 01:23:11,040
Who put this here?

705
01:23:13,340 --> 01:23:14,250
What's up?

706
01:23:15,050 --> 01:23:18,550
I could swear I just saw Satsuki and Mei
laughing up in that pine tree.

707
01:23:21,510 --> 01:23:23,760
It sounds crazy but maybe you did. Look.

